        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:lang="am">
                <note>The following subdivision and incipits are taken from <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BLorient12034">London, British Library, BL Oriental 12034</ref>, quoted according to the
                    catalogue description in <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/RSEA4WPK"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1978BritishLibrary"/><title level="m">Catalogue of Ethiopian Manuscripts in the British Library acquired since the Year 1877</title><author><forename>Stefan</forename><surname>Strelcyn</surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>British Museum</publisher><date>1978</date><note type="tags"><note type="tag">Ethiopic</note><note type="tag">Cataloguing</note><note type="tag">British Museum</note><note type="tag">bm:Strelcyn1978BritishLibrary</note></note><note type="tag">Ethiopic</note><note type="tag">Cataloguing</note><note type="tag">British Museum</note><note type="tag">bm:Strelcyn1978BritishLibrary</note><citedRange unit="page">148</citedRange></bibl>.</note>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="textsubunit" xml:id="Thief">
                    <label>Prescription to find a thief</label>
                    <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit">
                        <ab>የሌባ፡ ምራ፡</ab>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="textsubunit" xml:id="Pregnant">
                    <label>Prescription for a woman who cannot get pregnant and has irregular menstruation</label>
                    <note>Indicated as a prescription "against vaginal haemorrhage of a pregnant woman" in 
                        <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/RSEA4WPK"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1978BritishLibrary"/><title level="m">Catalogue of Ethiopian Manuscripts in the British Library acquired since the Year 1877</title><author><forename>Stefan</forename><surname>Strelcyn</surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>British Museum</publisher><date>1978</date><note type="tags"><note type="tag">Ethiopic</note><note type="tag">Cataloguing</note><note type="tag">British Museum</note><note type="tag">bm:Strelcyn1978BritishLibrary</note></note><note type="tag">Ethiopic</note><note type="tag">Cataloguing</note><note type="tag">British Museum</note><note type="tag">bm:Strelcyn1978BritishLibrary</note><citedRange unit="page">148</citedRange></bibl>.</note>
                    <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit">
                        <ab>የደም፡ ልጅ፡ እምቢ፡ ላላት፡ እንበለ፡ ወራቱ፡ ደም፡ ለሚመፃበት፡</ab>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="textsubunit" xml:id="Buda">
                    <label>Prescription against Budā</label>
                    <note>On <foreign xml:lang="gez">Budā</foreign> cf. 
                        <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/H8WBU22B"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1972Wellcome"/><title level="a">Catalogue of Ethiopian Manuscripts of the Wellcome Institute of the History of Medicine in London</title><title level="j">Bulletin of the School of Oriental and African Studies, University of London</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Stefan</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Strelcyn</t:surname></author><date>1972</date><biblScope unit="volume">35</biblScope><biblScope unit="issue">1</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">27-55</biblScope><note type="url">http://www.jstor.org/stable/612793</note><citedRange unit="page">44</citedRange></bibl>.</note>
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="textsubunit" xml:id="Dog">
                    <label>Prescription for a man bitten by a mad dog</label>
                    <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit">
                        <ab>እብድ፡ ውሻ፡ ለነከሰው፡</ab>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="textsubunit" xml:id="All">
                    <label>Prescriptions against all diseases</label>
                    <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit">
                        <ab>ከደዌ፡ ሁሉ፡</ab>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="textsubunit" xml:id="Wounds">
                    <label>Prescription against wounds</label>
                    <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit">
                        <ab>"&gt;የለት፡ ቍስል፡</ab>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="textsubunit" xml:id="Teffi">
                    <label>Prescription against swelling, against inflammation or swelling of the eye</label>
                    <note>Cf. <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/7T7W7L3J"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1968Medecine"/><title level="m">Médecine et plantes d’Éthiopie. Les traités médicaux éthiopiens. Medycyna i zioła etiopskie. Etiopskie traktaty medyczne</title><title level="s">Prace Orientalistyczne</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Stefan</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Strelcyn</t:surname></author><pubPlace>Warszawa</pubPlace><publisher>Państwowe Wydawnictwo Naukowe</publisher><date>1968</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Prace Orientalistyczne</t:title></series><biblScope unit="volume">XIV</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">429</citedRange></bibl>.</note>
                    <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit">
                        <ab>"&gt;ለአበጠ፡ ለጥፊ፡</ab>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="textsubunit" xml:id="Placenta">
                    <label>Prescription for expelling the placenta</label>
                    <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit">
                        <ab>&gt;የእንግዴህ፡ ልጅ፡</ab>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="textsubunit" xml:id="Breasts">
                    <label>Prescription against the swelling of the breasts</label>
                    <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit">
                        <ab>"&gt;ጡቷም፡ ላበጠበት፡</ab>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="textsubunit" xml:id="Coitus">
                    <label>For a woman who has an aversion to her (own) vagina</label>
                    <note>Indicated as prescription "for a man after coitus" in 
                        <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/RSEA4WPK"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1978BritishLibrary"/><title level="m">Catalogue of Ethiopian Manuscripts in the British Library acquired since the Year 1877</title><author><forename>Stefan</forename><surname>Strelcyn</surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>British Museum</publisher><date>1978</date><note type="tags"><note type="tag">Ethiopic</note><note type="tag">Cataloguing</note><note type="tag">British Museum</note><note type="tag">bm:Strelcyn1978BritishLibrary</note></note><note type="tag">Ethiopic</note><note type="tag">Cataloguing</note><note type="tag">British Museum</note><note type="tag">bm:Strelcyn1978BritishLibrary</note><citedRange unit="page">148</citedRange></bibl>, but probably
                        rather "for a man who has an aversion to her (woman's) genitals".</note>
                    <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit">
                        <ab>ብልቷንም፡ ለሰቀቀው<supplied reason="omitted">፡</supplied> ሰው፡</ab>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography">
                
            </div>
        </body>
